// Experiment No.2: Formatting and Organizing Content on a Web Page 

// a. Create a web page using HTML. 
b. Format content using tables, hyperlinks, and images. 
c. Organize information using ordered and unordered lists for a structured and readable page. 

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Sample Web Page</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 1.6;
            margin: 30px;
        }

        table {
            border-collapse: collapse;
            width: 80%;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        table, th, td {
            border: 1px solid black;
            padding: 8px;
        }

        th {
            background-color: #F2F2F2;
        }

        img {
            width: 200px;
            height: auto;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Sample Web Page</h1>

    <h2>1. Using a Table</h2>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Subject</th>
            <th>Teacher</th>
            <th>Room</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Mathematics</td>
            <td>Mrs. Sharma</td>
            <td>TD-101</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Science</td>
            <td>Mr. Rao</td>
            <td>TD-102</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>History</td>
            <td>
<td>Mr. Patel</td>
<td>103</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
<h1 title="Hyperlinks">Hyperlinks</h1>
<a href="https://www.wikipedia.org" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a> for more information.
</p>
<p>
<h2 title="Image">Image</h2>
<p>Here is an example image:</p>
<img src="sample.jpg" alt="Sample Image">
</p>
<h2 title="Ordered List">Ordered List</h2>
<ol>
<li>Wake up early</li>
<li>Have breakfast</li>
<li>Attend class</li>
<li>Complete homework</li>
</ol>
<h2 title="Unordered List">Unordered List</h2>
<ul>
<li>Fruits
<ul>
<li>Apple</li>
<li>Banana</li>
<li>Orange</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Vegetables
<ul>
<li>Carrot</li>
<li>Spinach</li>
<li>Tomato</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>
